            "answer_text": "Not by the narrator, no. But the word might occur in dialogue. Third person means you write: She lived happily ever after. he lived happily ever after. They lived happily ever after. First person means you write: We lived happily ever after. (or I lived happily ever after, but he was miserable.) ",
